1
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:16,809
CAREFUL - NARROW ROAD

2
00:00:19,979 --> 00:00:21,188
Diane?

3
00:00:26,318 --> 00:00:27,778
What?

4
00:00:48,466 --> 00:00:51,093
-Chloe.
-Emma.

5
00:00:54,972 --> 00:00:58,100
Hear me out, Simon.

6
00:00:58,184 --> 00:00:59,185
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

7
00:00:59,268 --> 00:01:02,271
Chloe's so mean to me.

8
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:03,522
What's the matter?

9
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:07,818
Yesterday, Chloe gave me
some foreign snacks.

10
00:01:07,902 --> 00:01:10,821
Guess what she said
as she handed them over?

11
00:01:11,864 --> 00:01:15,201
"It tastes terrible.
Miss Emma, it's yours."

12
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:23,083
Usually, you'd only gift food
you like, right?

13
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:26,796
But she gave me something she didn't like.
Is she mocking me?

14
00:01:29,173 --> 00:01:31,884
She may not have liked it,

15
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:34,094
but maybe she thought you would.

16
00:01:34,637 --> 00:01:37,431
That's what she said too.

17
00:01:37,515 --> 00:01:41,435
When I bit into it,
it tasted like toothpaste.

18
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:42,686
Really now.

19
00:01:43,771 --> 00:01:45,064
To begin with,

20
00:01:45,147 --> 00:01:49,068
I absolutely hate throwing food away.

21
00:01:49,151 --> 00:01:51,529
I hate gossiping.

22
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:54,406
But because she gave it to me,

23
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:57,284
I have to be the one to throw it away.

24
00:01:57,368 --> 00:02:01,497
She's making me do an unpleasant task…

25
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:04,124
-It spoils the vibe.
-…she was supposed to do herself.

26
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:07,127
What do you think?

27
00:02:10,923 --> 00:02:13,759
Then bring it to me.

28
00:02:14,718 --> 00:02:16,595
It may be nasty by itself,

29
00:02:16,679 --> 00:02:20,057
but that may not be the case
if it's paired with something else.

30
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:23,394
It could spice up
the overall flavor profile.

31
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:26,313
You're so kind, Simon.

32
00:02:28,691 --> 00:02:30,025
But Chloe

33
00:02:30,109 --> 00:02:33,362
would never give you food
if she thought it was terrible.

34
00:02:34,071 --> 00:02:37,074
She looks down on me, I just know it.

35
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,201
Come on, that's not true.

36
00:02:39,285 --> 00:02:40,953
At the end of the day,

37
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:43,289
she has all the resources in the world.

38
00:02:43,372 --> 00:02:46,834
She wouldn't understand
how someone like me feels,

39
00:02:46,917 --> 00:02:48,878
even if she meant no harm.

40
00:02:53,757 --> 00:02:56,010
-Welcome in.
-Welcome in-- Shoot.

41
00:02:57,553 --> 00:02:58,929
Shoot?

42
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:02,516
You sound like you've been up to something
behind the owner's back.

43
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,184
I was not.

44
00:03:09,523 --> 00:03:10,774
Coffee, please.

45
00:03:10,858 --> 00:03:11,984
Coming right up.

46
00:03:16,071 --> 00:03:17,323
Miss Emma,

47
00:03:17,406 --> 00:03:21,201
I told you from the start to wash
the underwear separately.

48
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:23,787
What? I do.

49
00:03:23,871 --> 00:03:24,955
No, you don't.

50
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:27,958
I noticed you only run
the washer once, so I looked today.

51
00:03:28,042 --> 00:03:29,835
You toss all the laundry into one wash.

52
00:03:30,336 --> 00:03:32,922
I put the underwear in a laundry net.

53
00:03:33,005 --> 00:03:34,173
That doesn't count.

54
00:03:36,383 --> 00:03:41,180
In your mind,
using the laundry net was enough.

55
00:03:41,263 --> 00:03:42,348
That's right.

56
00:03:42,431 --> 00:03:44,808
It's technically separate, right?

57
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:49,021
That's not the point.
Please run two separate cycles.

58
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:50,731
Okay then.

59
00:03:52,066 --> 00:03:53,067
Listen…

60
00:03:54,652 --> 00:03:55,694
Hey.

61
00:03:55,778 --> 00:03:57,947
-Welcome in.
-Welcome in.

62
00:04:11,043 --> 00:04:12,211
What's this?

63
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:17,007
Choshu, Handa,
you're sitting separately today?

64
00:04:17,091 --> 00:04:19,301
-One coffee, please.
-Okay.

65
00:04:19,385 --> 00:04:21,470
A cafe au lait for me.

66
00:04:21,553 --> 00:04:22,596
Of course.

67
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,556
That's "café" au lait.

68
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:26,016
You're annoying me.

69
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,352
One "café" for me.

70
00:04:29,144 --> 00:04:31,897
-Hear me out, boss.
-Yes?

71
00:04:31,981 --> 00:04:34,942
It's like he thinks he's better than me.

72
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:36,485
He won't quit nagging me

73
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:40,781
to learn how to use
a messaging app and stuff.

74
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:44,076
That's because you said
you finally bought a smartphone.

75
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:46,954
I'm only teaching you out of kindness.

76
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:49,957
I only need it to make calls, that's it.

77
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:51,750
How aggravating, huh?

78
00:04:51,834 --> 00:04:55,170
Look at you,
dragging others into it again.

79
00:04:56,005 --> 00:04:57,131
Zip it.

80
00:04:57,631 --> 00:04:59,675
Please calm down, you two.

81
00:05:01,719 --> 00:05:02,761
Welcome in.

82
00:05:02,845 --> 00:05:04,179
Matthew?

83
00:05:05,723 --> 00:05:07,599
Miss Chloe, thank goodness you're here.

84
00:05:09,393 --> 00:05:10,644
Did you need to talk to me?

85
00:05:10,728 --> 00:05:14,231
I wanted to talk to you about something.

86
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:16,442
I was hoping you could
perform a fortune reading.

87
00:05:16,525 --> 00:05:19,820
Sorry, she only reads fortunes on Sundays.

88
00:05:19,903 --> 00:05:22,156
Oh, right.

89
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:24,575
Are you off today, Matthew?

90
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:26,368
Yes, it's Saturday.

91
00:05:26,452 --> 00:05:30,122
But sometimes I work over the weekend
if I have a meeting with a client.

92
00:05:30,205 --> 00:05:31,457
Thank you.

93
00:05:41,258 --> 00:05:44,261
I'll at least hear you out.

94
00:05:45,471 --> 00:05:46,638
Will you really?

95
00:05:47,765 --> 00:05:51,435
So, it's about Diane.

96
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:52,978
Diane?

97
00:05:53,062 --> 00:05:54,063
Yes.

98
00:05:54,146 --> 00:05:57,608
I spotted Diane
on the way to the office today.

99
00:05:58,233 --> 00:06:00,861
I thought, "Huh, we're closed today."

100
00:06:00,944 --> 00:06:03,697
Then, a parked car's door swung open.

101
00:06:03,781 --> 00:06:05,991
Before I knew it, they grabbed her.

102
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:12,331
Then the car sped away.

103
00:06:13,999 --> 00:06:15,292
Sounds like trouble, right?

104
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:19,922
That's an incident.
You don't need a fortune teller.

105
00:06:20,839 --> 00:06:23,801
Yes, that's true.

106
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,135
It could be an incident.

107
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,846
This is bad news.

108
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:29,181
Trouble's stirring.

109
00:06:30,349 --> 00:06:32,559
I--Is it an incident?

110
00:06:32,643 --> 00:06:33,727
It absolutely is.

111
00:06:34,311 --> 00:06:35,312
What?

112
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:40,776
What kind of car was it?

113
00:06:41,276 --> 00:06:43,946
Do you remember anything,
like the license plate number?

114
00:06:44,029 --> 00:06:45,864
It all happened so quickly.

115
00:06:45,948 --> 00:06:48,283
I didn't see the perpetrator
or the plate number.

116
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:50,744
I think it was a black van, though.

117
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:53,455
Where was it headed?

118
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:56,750
I chased it for a bit on my bicycle.

119
00:06:56,834 --> 00:06:58,627
It was headed toward Hachioji.

120
00:06:58,710 --> 00:06:59,837
I see.

121
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:03,590
Okay, you were riding a bicycle.

122
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:07,427
Cho, is that relevant?

123
00:07:08,137 --> 00:07:09,513
-No?
-No.

124
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:12,850
Have you tried contacting her?
Like, did you try texting?

125
00:07:14,143 --> 00:07:16,603
I called, but she didn't pick up.

126
00:07:17,187 --> 00:07:18,355
You called her?

127
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:21,984
If she's been kidnapped,
do you think she can pick up?

128
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:24,486
That's a good point.

129
00:07:25,696 --> 00:07:28,115
I'll send her a message now,
just so we can rule it out.

130
00:07:32,286 --> 00:07:34,580
They were headed to Hachioji…

131
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,748
That's toward Okutama, right?

132
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,168
Okutama…

133
00:07:40,169 --> 00:07:41,211
Okutama!

134
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:46,216
The Okutama serial kidnapping and killing
of women everyone's talking about.

135
00:07:47,009 --> 00:07:50,095
A woman who was taken
in a van was found dead.

136
00:07:50,179 --> 00:07:53,056
That woman was snatched in Shibuya.

137
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:55,976
Your office is located
in Yoyogi-Uehara, right?

138
00:07:56,059 --> 00:07:57,102
That's in Shibuya ward.

139
00:07:59,313 --> 00:08:01,648
Oh, what? B-b-b-b-but…

140
00:08:01,732 --> 00:08:04,693
the victim was a young woman.

141
00:08:04,776 --> 00:08:06,695
So Diane can't be their target, right?

142
00:08:09,156 --> 00:08:11,617
No, Matthew…

143
00:08:17,289 --> 00:08:19,708
Oh, Diane responded.

144
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:22,920
She says she's okay.

145
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:28,842
DIANE - I'M OKAY

146
00:08:30,761 --> 00:08:32,387
Thank goodness.

147
00:08:32,888 --> 00:08:34,806
What a relief.

148
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:36,475
Seriously.

149
00:08:36,558 --> 00:08:38,185
I'll ask who she's with right now.

150
00:08:40,229 --> 00:08:43,523
So it's nothing sinister, right?

151
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:50,822
Sorry, I don't mean to scare you,

152
00:08:50,906 --> 00:08:55,244
but what exactly did she mean by "okay"?

153
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:03,335
She might have meant,
"Don't worry about me,"

154
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:06,463
or, "I'm safe from danger…"

155
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:11,176
So, her life's not in danger,
at least for now?

156
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:13,971
Could that be
what she meant by she's okay?

157
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,724
Well,

158
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:22,729
I feel like she's okay.
She said so herself.

159
00:09:23,397 --> 00:09:27,025
But we should also consider
the worst-case scenario.

160
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:36,618
No response.

161
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:38,954
What should we do?

162
00:09:40,831 --> 00:09:44,960
I know. It's time
for your fortune-telling to shine.

163
00:09:46,962 --> 00:09:50,048
I don't give out predictions
like Nathan Shingetsu.

164
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:56,096
It might help
move the situation forward, at least.

165
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:02,936
I see your point.

166
00:10:04,438 --> 00:10:07,441
Let's calm down and sort things out.

167
00:10:08,483 --> 00:10:09,609
Thank you so much.

168
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:13,947
Simon, let's close shop for the day.

169
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:15,824
Yes.

170
00:10:17,492 --> 00:10:18,952
Well, we should get going.

171
00:10:19,036 --> 00:10:20,329
Yeah.

172
00:10:21,038 --> 00:10:23,206
-Thanks for the coffee.
-Yeah, thanks.

173
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,292
-Thank you for your patronage.
-Thank you.

174
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,677
Oh, mon…

175
00:10:35,761 --> 00:10:36,970
Dieu!

176
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:40,474
What are you doing?

177
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,100
Shh, Matthew.

178
00:10:55,572 --> 00:10:58,909
Miss Emma, please pick up the rest later.

179
00:10:58,992 --> 00:11:01,203
Only one card today?

180
00:11:01,286 --> 00:11:02,996
We're just reading her present.

181
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:13,715
This card represents
Rika Diane's current situation.

182
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:21,306
SEPTEMBER

183
00:11:22,182 --> 00:11:25,310
September, reversed. Card of Reflection.

184
00:11:27,187 --> 00:11:30,816
It looks like she has some regrets
about an unfavorable situation.

185
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:36,571
This card's key words.
Cardinal direction, east.

186
00:11:36,655 --> 00:11:39,116
The lucky color, gray.

187
00:11:39,908 --> 00:11:41,451
The location, a farm.

188
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:43,995
A farm?

189
00:11:46,289 --> 00:11:50,710
That reminds me. The largest farm
in all of Tokyo is located in Okutama.

190
00:11:57,134 --> 00:11:58,593
Could this be it?

191
00:11:58,677 --> 00:12:00,637
It says Nishitama, which is to the west.

192
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,888
That's right.

193
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:05,142
But the card indicates east.

194
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,226
OUKEI FARM

195
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:08,562
The farm is to the west.

196
00:12:09,354 --> 00:12:12,107
To be more precise,
it's northwest from here.

197
00:12:13,358 --> 00:12:16,820
Not all of a card's key words apply.

198
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:19,364
It's that one of its many meanings
might fit the situation.

199
00:12:19,865 --> 00:12:21,950
Then, it's up to
the fortune teller and the client

200
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:24,411
to work together
to decide how to interpret the cards.

201
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:36,465
Let's go to the police.

202
00:12:36,548 --> 00:12:38,467
What? But…

203
00:12:39,384 --> 00:12:42,304
After all, it's true
that Matthew saw her get kidnapped

204
00:12:42,387 --> 00:12:44,931
and she stopped responding.

205
00:12:45,015 --> 00:12:46,766
If this isn't an incident,

206
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:50,187
then we'll apologize
for the trouble we caused later.

207
00:12:50,979 --> 00:12:53,899
We don't want to regret
not taking action sooner.

208
00:12:57,068 --> 00:12:59,154
Yes. Let's go.

209
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:02,449
Shibuya ward, which means…

210
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:04,826
Shibuya Police Department?

211
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,078
That's where we should go, right?

212
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:25,013
Shibuya Police Department…
that's this way.

213
00:13:30,936 --> 00:13:32,229
Actually, Chloe.

214
00:13:34,397 --> 00:13:36,733
Will you go on without me?

215
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:38,568
Huh? Why?

216
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:39,903
Well…

217
00:13:40,612 --> 00:13:42,781
I want to stop by the electronics store.

218
00:13:44,908 --> 00:13:48,286
An acquaintance of yours
could be in deep trouble,

219
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,996
and that's what you want to do?

220
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:52,707
I mean, I'm worried about her,

221
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:56,211
but I've been wanting
a portable fan that goes around my neck.

222
00:13:56,294 --> 00:13:58,588
A portable fan?

223
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:01,383
You can buy it online at any time.

224
00:14:01,466 --> 00:14:04,344
I know, but…

225
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:08,515
I don't want parcels arriving
in my name when I'm boarding rent-free.

226
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:11,935
I don't know Diane the way you guys do.

227
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:14,646
I may not be much help
even if I tag along.

228
00:14:16,314 --> 00:14:18,316
Emma, listen…

229
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,943
She's right, you know.

230
00:14:20,944 --> 00:14:24,573
We'll do this ourselves.
Go run your errand, Emma.

231
00:14:24,656 --> 00:14:27,367
Sorry. Thank you for understanding.

232
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,369
I'll join you as soon as I'm done.

233
00:14:29,452 --> 00:14:30,579
Well, bye.

234
00:14:36,585 --> 00:14:40,338
Seems like Emma is trying
to be considerate in her own way.

235
00:14:41,298 --> 00:14:43,300
So am I.

236
00:14:43,383 --> 00:14:45,176
I'm considerate of her too.

237
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:56,104
When there's a power imbalance,

238
00:14:56,187 --> 00:14:59,816
I have to be careful I don't come
across as annoying or unlikable.

239
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,861
Still, you have to be assertive to get by.

240
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:06,656
When a tiny woman like me
is quiet, I get bulldozed over.

241
00:15:16,207 --> 00:15:18,084
Speaking of,

242
00:15:18,168 --> 00:15:21,421
I try too hard and end up blowing it.

243
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:26,676
Matthew, yours isn't a matter
of being considerate or not.

244
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,720
You're just really insensitive.

245
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:31,306
What? Come on, that's not true.

246
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:36,895
It'd be best if both of you
could be more open with each other.

247
00:15:37,562 --> 00:15:38,938
You think so?

248
00:15:39,022 --> 00:15:42,108
Nothing irritates me
more than inconsiderate people.

249
00:15:42,192 --> 00:15:44,319
Diane must be

250
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:47,864
such an understanding person
to keep you around.

251
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:52,077
Well, but…

252
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,954
So what if Emma doesn't join us?

253
00:15:55,038 --> 00:15:56,915
She hardly knows Diane anyway.

254
00:15:59,209 --> 00:16:00,293
Still…

255
00:16:03,588 --> 00:16:04,673
Still,

256
00:16:05,382 --> 00:16:09,135
she may not be much help,
but she can still tag along.

257
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:18,269
Miss Chloe, you were only hoping
for Emma to stick by you.

258
00:16:19,354 --> 00:16:20,355
What?

259
00:16:20,897 --> 00:16:22,273
It's fine.

260
00:16:22,357 --> 00:16:25,360
If you ever need someone to rely on,
you can always count on me.

261
00:16:25,443 --> 00:16:29,030
That's the most unreliable thing
I've heard in all my life.

262
00:16:29,114 --> 00:16:30,240
What?

263
00:16:39,582 --> 00:16:41,084
Oh, it's Emma.

264
00:16:45,130 --> 00:16:46,256
What is it?

265
00:16:47,549 --> 00:16:51,386
"Is this her?" in all lower-case.

266
00:16:52,846 --> 00:16:55,640
IS THIS HER?

267
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:58,184
Could she be referring
to "Daian" the comedian duo?

268
00:16:58,268 --> 00:17:00,270
They could be staging a shoot
to buy home appliances.

269
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:02,313
She'd text about that right now?

270
00:17:03,815 --> 00:17:06,025
IS THIS DIANE?

271
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:07,527
Is that…

272
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:10,697
a sumo ring?

273
00:17:17,954 --> 00:17:18,955
What?

274
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:20,749
That's Diane, isn't it?

275
00:17:29,174 --> 00:17:31,176
Hello? Emma?

276
00:17:31,259 --> 00:17:32,927
Hello? Chloe?

277
00:17:33,678 --> 00:17:38,057
I just passed by the TV section, and I saw
someone who looks a lot like Diane, in 4K.

278
00:17:38,808 --> 00:17:40,810
Sumo matches are broadcasted live, right?

279
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:42,979
Right…

280
00:17:43,938 --> 00:17:47,692
I'll try calling her now. I'm hanging up.

281
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:49,611
Sure.

282
00:17:52,906 --> 00:17:55,533
Diane…

283
00:17:58,411 --> 00:17:59,537
Hello?

284
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:14,677
She's watching sumo. She's okay.

285
00:18:15,512 --> 00:18:17,639
Well, I'm glad she's safe.

286
00:18:17,722 --> 00:18:19,432
Yes. Thank heavens.

287
00:18:19,516 --> 00:18:21,100
Sorry for the trouble.

288
00:18:21,184 --> 00:18:22,310
Ah, no.

289
00:18:23,895 --> 00:18:25,063
I'm wiped.

290
00:18:25,939 --> 00:18:28,608
I'm gonna blow off steam
through shopping, then I'll go home.

291
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:30,151
Sure.

292
00:18:30,235 --> 00:18:31,611
Sorry about the trouble.

293
00:18:58,429 --> 00:19:00,390
Emma's got it rough.

294
00:19:01,266 --> 00:19:03,560
Is that how she has to be
on a daily basis?

295
00:19:10,024 --> 00:19:11,109
Is something the matter?

296
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:16,155
Those two…

297
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,992
They do this to each other.

298
00:19:20,451 --> 00:19:23,538
It's as if they've drawn a hard line
and are set on not crossing it.

299
00:19:24,831 --> 00:19:26,958
And I just think…

300
00:19:28,251 --> 00:19:29,961
that it's a bit unfortunate.

301
00:19:30,044 --> 00:19:31,087
Unfortunate?

302
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:37,760
I wish those two could learn to get along

303
00:19:39,095 --> 00:19:41,014
without having to draw a line.

304
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:45,059
I can relate.

305
00:19:45,143 --> 00:19:48,396
I hate confrontations.

306
00:19:48,479 --> 00:19:52,191
When a situation
becomes tense, I start pulling away.

307
00:19:52,275 --> 00:19:53,484
Really?

308
00:19:54,736 --> 00:19:55,945
But you have a point.

309
00:19:56,487 --> 00:19:59,324
Maybe that's unfortunate too.

310
00:20:01,993 --> 00:20:05,371
I hate it when the conversation drops,
and it gets silent.

311
00:20:05,997 --> 00:20:10,585
I start blabbering on about people's
personal lives to fill the silence.

312
00:20:10,668 --> 00:20:13,087
So that's why Chloe
called you insensitive.

313
00:20:13,171 --> 00:20:15,340
Yeah, that's why.

314
00:20:19,844 --> 00:20:23,139
Have you been working
at Diane's office for long?

315
00:20:23,681 --> 00:20:24,766
I have.

316
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:28,645
I've worked at that office
since her father was in charge.

317
00:20:28,728 --> 00:20:30,563
Wow, that long?

318
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:35,193
Both Diane and her father
must be very understanding.

319
00:20:37,362 --> 00:20:38,363
What?

320
00:20:39,197 --> 00:20:40,281
Huh?

321
00:20:41,449 --> 00:20:42,742
That's not what I meant.

322
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:45,787
Sorry.

323
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:48,456
That was insensitive of me.

324
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:53,878
But there's one thing
Diane always says to me.

325
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:58,925
She says my personality is so intense
that it keeps things spiced up.

326
00:20:59,008 --> 00:21:00,593
-Spiced up?
-Yes.

327
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:04,180
Spice, huh.

328
00:21:06,099 --> 00:21:08,518
I talked about spice this morning too.

329
00:21:09,185 --> 00:21:10,895
Though it was in regards to parfaits.

330
00:21:10,979 --> 00:21:12,897
-Parfaits?
-Yes.

331
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:16,442
Take a strong and mild ingredient…

332
00:21:17,318 --> 00:21:21,906
and find the perfect ratio
so they don't clash.

333
00:21:22,573 --> 00:21:25,910
It's about making each ingredient shine.

334
00:21:27,662 --> 00:21:29,205
I see.

335
00:21:30,498 --> 00:21:31,791
Doesn't make any sense, does it?

336
00:21:31,874 --> 00:21:33,292
No, it does.

337
00:21:38,631 --> 00:21:39,757
Maybe…

338
00:21:41,009 --> 00:21:42,635
that's the same with people.

339
00:21:53,104 --> 00:21:55,398
Dear passengers,

340
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:58,234
there's a trespasser on the railway.

341
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:01,487
Due to safety concerns, we will
momentarily suspend our operations.

342
00:22:01,571 --> 00:22:05,241
We apologize for any inconvenience
this may cause.

343
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:08,494
Please standby for operations to resume.

344
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:11,289
As in, someone
crossed onto the train tracks?

345
00:22:11,372 --> 00:22:13,708
Not sure. Could be the platform.

346
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:15,793
Huh? How does that make sense?

347
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:22,050
Apparently, a groper tried to escape
onto the tracks, and trains are suspended.

348
00:22:22,592 --> 00:22:24,427
What? Seriously?

349
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:27,180
This was near Mitaka station.

350
00:22:27,972 --> 00:22:29,098
Mitaka, huh.

351
00:22:29,807 --> 00:22:31,517
We might be here for a while.

352
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:33,352
Thank you.

353
00:22:33,936 --> 00:22:35,063
Don't mention it.

354
00:22:36,189 --> 00:22:38,441
If the groper ran away, is he innocent?

355
00:22:38,524 --> 00:22:40,735
No, he's got to be guilty.

356
00:22:40,818 --> 00:22:42,320
I'm irritated.

357
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:47,283
Sex offenders have a high recurrence rate.
They should all be behind bars for life.

358
00:22:49,035 --> 00:22:52,914
Actually, thieves have higher
recurrence rates than sex offenders.

359
00:22:53,748 --> 00:22:55,166
-What?
-What?

360
00:22:55,249 --> 00:22:58,669
Oh, sorry to butt in.

361
00:22:58,753 --> 00:23:02,673
But don't they say sex offenders
have high recurrence rates?

362
00:23:03,549 --> 00:23:08,262
I heard that, and looked into it.

363
00:23:08,346 --> 00:23:12,308
In regards to
recurrence rates, sex offense's

364
00:23:12,391 --> 00:23:15,228
is less than half of theft's.

365
00:23:15,311 --> 00:23:17,105
Huh, didn't expect that.

366
00:23:17,939 --> 00:23:19,899
According to Ministry of Justice's

367
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:23,736
official 2024 report on recidivism rates,

368
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:26,989
nonconsensual sex is 2.4 percent,

369
00:23:27,073 --> 00:23:30,201
molesting is 5.2 percent,

370
00:23:30,284 --> 00:23:33,746
and theft is 17.1 percent.

371
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:37,375
Thank you for the information.

372
00:23:38,042 --> 00:23:41,170
Sorry, I wanted to see the actual numbers.

373
00:23:41,796 --> 00:23:44,298
The way she fills in is hilarious.

374
00:23:47,385 --> 00:23:51,097
In the U.S., sexual offenders
are listed on an online registry.

375
00:23:51,597 --> 00:23:54,142
The ex-cons become targets
of online hate comments

376
00:23:54,225 --> 00:23:55,560
and even gun violence.

377
00:23:55,643 --> 00:23:56,853
Wow…

378
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:02,984
A city where sex offenders' addresses are
publicly known, and one where they're not.

379
00:24:04,277 --> 00:24:07,113
Supposing both cities have
the same rates of sex-related offenses,

380
00:24:07,196 --> 00:24:10,283
I wonder which city would
make you feel safer.

381
00:24:10,992 --> 00:24:13,452
I can protect myself better if I knew.

382
00:24:13,536 --> 00:24:15,454
I prefer a city
where sex offenders are listed.

383
00:24:15,538 --> 00:24:18,291
They're ex-cons.
In other words, returning citizens.

384
00:24:18,374 --> 00:24:19,959
You devil's advocate.

385
00:24:20,042 --> 00:24:23,129
Why do you always side
with gropers and sexual predators?

386
00:24:23,212 --> 00:24:24,463
Are you a groper?

387
00:24:24,547 --> 00:24:28,926
Of course not. I'm just pointing out
the possibility of a wrongful conviction.

388
00:24:30,136 --> 00:24:31,137
Say…

389
00:24:31,637 --> 00:24:33,848
Here comes the lady with more info.

390
00:24:33,931 --> 00:24:37,226
The groper on the run
has been apprehended.

391
00:24:37,310 --> 00:24:39,103
What? Yes!

392
00:24:39,187 --> 00:24:41,606
The train should start moving.
What a relief.

393
00:24:43,024 --> 00:24:44,192
Thank you.

394
00:24:44,984 --> 00:24:48,529
It's fine. I was browsing online anyway.

395
00:24:49,572 --> 00:24:50,656
They tackled him?

396
00:24:51,199 --> 00:24:53,534
Dear passengers.

397
00:24:53,618 --> 00:24:56,704
We apologize for the inconvenience.

398
00:24:56,787 --> 00:25:01,375
We've received information that
the trespasser has been apprehended.

399
00:25:01,876 --> 00:25:04,128
We will resume operations soon.

400
00:25:08,758 --> 00:25:11,928
There's no right answer, is there?

401
00:25:15,097 --> 00:25:17,892
The criminals' information too.

402
00:25:19,435 --> 00:25:24,273
But it's not possible
to be objectively right or wrong.

403
00:25:25,775 --> 00:25:28,945
Sometimes, an answer
that felt right in the moment

404
00:25:29,028 --> 00:25:31,364
may feel wrong after a while.

405
00:25:34,033 --> 00:25:36,452
When it comes to things
without a right answer,

406
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:39,247
I believe you must follow your feelings.

407
00:25:40,122 --> 00:25:43,376
You have to believe in yourself,
and press forward.

408
00:25:53,219 --> 00:25:57,181
Thank you for your patience.
We will now resume operations.

409
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:16,033
Perhaps that applies
to fortune-telling too.

410
00:26:17,368 --> 00:26:18,369
Come again?

411
00:26:19,245 --> 00:26:21,163
There's no such thing as a right answer.

412
00:26:24,375 --> 00:26:26,252
A single fortune-telling card

413
00:26:26,335 --> 00:26:27,920
can represent various things.

414
00:26:28,546 --> 00:26:31,882
We choose its meaning according
to the person and their circumstance.

415
00:26:32,883 --> 00:26:34,552
The interpretation shifts

416
00:26:35,136 --> 00:26:39,598
depending on the meaning we choose
and the words we use.

417
00:26:42,018 --> 00:26:43,311
Fortune-telling, huh?

418
00:26:45,229 --> 00:26:46,564
I find it scary.

419
00:26:48,941 --> 00:26:50,067
Scary?

420
00:26:50,985 --> 00:26:54,697
When someone in authority declares,

421
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:59,744
"This is who you are,"
you can't help but be aware of it.

422
00:27:02,580 --> 00:27:07,710
If you're told you're diligent,
you needlessly push yourself.

423
00:27:07,793 --> 00:27:09,003
The opposite is also true.

424
00:27:10,963 --> 00:27:14,300
If you're told you give up easily,

425
00:27:14,383 --> 00:27:16,677
you throw in the towel
before you even get started.

426
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:21,349
We get tied up by the words we use
before we realize it.

427
00:27:23,225 --> 00:27:27,480
To me, that's almost like a curse.

428
00:27:31,192 --> 00:27:34,362
Can't you say the same thing

429
00:27:34,904 --> 00:27:37,239
about how your parents and teachers
describe you?

430
00:27:39,617 --> 00:27:41,869
Yes, I agree.

431
00:27:42,703 --> 00:27:44,455
It's not exclusive to fortune-telling.

432
00:27:48,584 --> 00:27:51,670
Words are tricky and frightening,

433
00:27:53,047 --> 00:27:54,965
but that makes them
all the more intriguing.

434
00:27:57,676 --> 00:27:58,844
It's almost like magic.

435
00:28:20,616 --> 00:28:23,327
I'm sorry for the trouble I caused.

436
00:28:23,411 --> 00:28:26,122
No, I'm glad nothing bad happened to you.

437
00:28:26,205 --> 00:28:28,999
You're right about that. Thank goodness.

438
00:28:29,083 --> 00:28:33,295
Here's your souvenir,
Kokugikan sumo ring chicken.

439
00:28:33,379 --> 00:28:36,632
This famous dish is made
down in the basement of Kokugikan.

440
00:28:37,633 --> 00:28:39,009
Thank you very much.

441
00:28:39,552 --> 00:28:40,719
Emma.

442
00:28:43,389 --> 00:28:44,640
Thank you.

443
00:28:45,141 --> 00:28:46,225
Join us.

444
00:28:46,308 --> 00:28:47,518
Thank you.

445
00:28:54,817 --> 00:28:57,945
Really, I don't know what to say.

446
00:28:58,028 --> 00:29:00,156
My ex-husband got up to his antics.

447
00:29:00,239 --> 00:29:04,034
I was so surprised.
They dragged you into the car.

448
00:29:04,118 --> 00:29:07,913
He did that here and there
when we were still together.

449
00:29:07,997 --> 00:29:11,333
I was pretty pissed off
about it this time around.

450
00:29:12,042 --> 00:29:13,419
Sumo out of the blue?

451
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:17,673
Two of the regular customers invited him.

452
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:20,926
The three of them planned on going,

453
00:29:21,010 --> 00:29:23,304
but one suddenly got sick,

454
00:29:23,387 --> 00:29:25,931
so they decided to bring me instead.

455
00:29:26,015 --> 00:29:29,393
We drove all the way to Hachioji
to get the tickets.

456
00:29:31,645 --> 00:29:32,897
Could it be?

457
00:29:39,487 --> 00:29:40,613
I knew it.

458
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:44,617
Everyone, from here to Ryogoku Kokugikan…

459
00:29:45,951 --> 00:29:47,703
is straight east.

460
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:48,913
RYOGOKU KOKUGIKAN

461
00:29:48,996 --> 00:29:50,247
It wasn't a farm.

462
00:29:50,331 --> 00:29:51,540
East?

463
00:29:51,624 --> 00:29:54,668
Chloe, your fortune-telling was spot-on.

464
00:29:54,752 --> 00:29:55,878
Whoa.

465
00:29:57,505 --> 00:30:01,258
Well then, everyone.
Thank you for waiting.

466
00:30:02,551 --> 00:30:05,137
Today, I made monochrome parfaits.

467
00:30:08,974 --> 00:30:10,684
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

468
00:30:11,477 --> 00:30:15,523
The black-and-white gradation
is very artistic. How pretty.

469
00:30:16,273 --> 00:30:19,568
From the bottom, lemon whipped cream,

470
00:30:19,652 --> 00:30:23,155
angel cake, and black sesame meringue.

471
00:30:23,239 --> 00:30:26,200
On the top is black sesame
and soy milk pudding,

472
00:30:26,283 --> 00:30:28,744
dark cherries, and black sesame gelato.

473
00:30:29,245 --> 00:30:32,998
Lastly, there's chocolate brownie
with blueberry ganache,

474
00:30:33,082 --> 00:30:35,668
topped with a feather
made of dark chocolate.

475
00:30:35,751 --> 00:30:37,211
Amazing.

476
00:30:37,294 --> 00:30:39,255
It's a piece of artwork.

477
00:30:40,089 --> 00:30:42,049
Bon appétit.

478
00:30:43,509 --> 00:30:44,718
Thank you.

479
00:30:52,935 --> 00:30:55,020
Yum. This is so delicious.

480
00:31:03,237 --> 00:31:04,280
Yum.

481
00:31:07,616 --> 00:31:10,703
This pudding is gray.
That's your lucky color.

482
00:31:13,414 --> 00:31:14,832
My lucky color?

483
00:31:15,416 --> 00:31:17,710
This is your auspicious parfait, Diane.

484
00:31:17,793 --> 00:31:19,587
Wow.

485
00:31:20,212 --> 00:31:21,672
I know. Simon.

486
00:31:23,674 --> 00:31:24,717
Yes?

487
00:31:26,677 --> 00:31:28,804
This is the nasty candy I told you about.

488
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:29,888
Whoa.

489
00:31:29,972 --> 00:31:32,474
You're giving away nasty candy?

490
00:31:32,558 --> 00:31:35,019
Right? You think so too?

491
00:31:35,102 --> 00:31:38,022
Hold on, Miss Emma. What was that, a jab?

492
00:31:38,105 --> 00:31:39,356
Chloe.

493
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:42,192
Then I'll tell you.

494
00:31:42,276 --> 00:31:44,612
While we were all worried
about Diane's safety,

495
00:31:44,695 --> 00:31:47,531
you went off to an electronics store
on your own. You're unbelievable.

496
00:31:47,615 --> 00:31:51,452
We only found Diane at the sumo ring
because of me.

497
00:31:51,535 --> 00:31:53,746
Besides, I wasn't that helpful.

498
00:31:53,829 --> 00:31:55,664
You're lucky it worked out in the end.

499
00:31:55,748 --> 00:31:58,709
To start, you're always like this.

500
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:01,128
Always like what?
Is this about the laundry again?

501
00:32:01,211 --> 00:32:03,797
Laundry too.

502
00:32:03,881 --> 00:32:05,758
A relationship is built

503
00:32:05,841 --> 00:32:08,052
by the people in it.

504
00:32:08,677 --> 00:32:10,596
Maybe my wish for them to get along

505
00:32:11,347 --> 00:32:15,309
comes from a selfish desire
of wanting to feel comfortable.

506
00:32:16,018 --> 00:32:20,022
The more we try to take control,
the more it becomes a struggle.

507
00:32:20,105 --> 00:32:21,106
But hey,

508
00:32:21,190 --> 00:32:25,402
we cracked the case
because I wanted to buy this. Right?

509
00:32:25,486 --> 00:32:27,988
It's true, but…

510
00:32:28,781 --> 00:32:30,658
Why don't you get it?

511
00:32:31,992 --> 00:32:35,954
Miss Chloe simply
wanted you to stick together.

512
00:32:36,038 --> 00:32:38,540
What? I never said that.

513
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:42,461
Huh? Is that right?

514
00:32:42,544 --> 00:32:43,837
Wrong.

515
00:32:44,630 --> 00:32:47,383
What? Come on, tell me the truth.

516
00:32:47,466 --> 00:32:48,717
Completely wrong.

517
00:33:10,781 --> 00:33:14,243
Should you have
brought him here, Mr. Shingetsu?

518
00:33:15,661 --> 00:33:19,164
There's nothing else
the doctors can do for him.

519
00:33:22,251 --> 00:33:24,878
I pushed you too hard, Gyo.

520
00:33:31,593 --> 00:33:33,971
Has the time come…

521
00:33:37,808 --> 00:33:38,851
Toma.

522
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:42,020
Yes?

523
00:33:44,314 --> 00:33:46,191
Find Sho.

524
00:33:48,610 --> 00:33:49,611
Yes.

525
00:36:13,130 --> 00:36:14,631
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

526
00:36:14,715 --> 00:36:16,717
Subtitle: Megumi Hunter
